may indicate that the trace amounts of igm originate in the fetus itself, but\par
transplacental passage has not been completely excluded.\par
the absence of immunoglobulin formation has been associated with the absence\par
of plasma cells in the lymphoid tissues and bone marrow of the normal human\par
fetus and the newborn.  it has been reported that these cells do not appear\par
until a few weeks after birth (2, 3, 14, 25, 34).  however, in pathological\par
